{
  "name": "RPlog_Aido_Or",
  "title": "Aido Or",
  "summary": "Returning to Karrde's compound on Myrkr aboard a slow repulsor skiff, the Jedi Jessalyn Valios and her student Orson Tighe are drawn by the Force to land beside a crystalline forest lake. Following an inexplicable compulsion deeper into the woods, Jessalyn discovers that a great ancient tree is in fact a sentient, Force-attuned being named Aido Or, which claims to have awaited the coming of Jedi for four hundred years. Aido Or invites Jessalyn to ask the question she has carried, and she asks whether the Jedi will rise again to bring peace. The creature foretells that the Jedi will indeed rise, then uproots itself and presents her with a spiny seed cone, charging her to plant its seeds on other worlds despite the price the Dark Side will demand. Shaken and awed, Jessalyn stows the cone and resolves to tell Luke as she and Orson head back at twilight.",
